26/10/2008
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Three Turkish engineers have been kidnapped in eastern Afghanistan's Khost province, Foreign Minister Rangin Dadfar Spanta announced on Saturday (October 25th). Two Afghani nationals, working with them at the Altinsan construction company, were also kidnapped. It happened on Wednesday afternoon, but police say they were not notified for hours. Turkish Foreign Minister Ali Babacan is making an official visit to Kabul and discussed the matter with Spanta on Saturday. (Zaman, AP, AFP, Reuters - 24/10/08)
